rComments: Very interesting and thought provoking lectures, and material. Clear grading rubric and assignments that give a lot of flexibility to introduce new ideas, argue and expand the current understanding of economic history. fair midterm/final

I genuine learned a lot from this class that I would not have known otherwise, and learned valuable data analysis skills.   If you like writing, this is your class.  Let me be clear; this is probably the ONLY 300 level eco course where there isn't a single drop of math or calc, NO MATH AT ALL.  It's all application and communication skills.

She didn't make child mortality any more interesting, but she possesses a great knowledge on the topic. Lectures are monotone, but she is able to generate some class discussion. Tests are quite hard but fair to those who have adequately prepared for them. Interesting material.
